Title: 2ZR-FXE (ENGINE MECHANICAL): CYLINDER BLOCK: INSPECTION; 2016 - 2022 MY Prius [11/2015 -        ]

INSPECTION

PROCEDURE

1. INSPECT CONNECTING ROD THRUST CLEARANCE

(a) Using a dial indicator, measure the thrust clearance while moving the connecting rod back and forth.

Standard Thrust Clearance:

Maximum Thrust Clearance

Specified Condition

0.342 mm

0.160 to 0.342 mm

0.0135 in.

0.00630 to 0.0135 in.

HINT:

If the thrust clearance is more than the maximum, replace the connecting rod. If necessary, replace the crankshaft.

2. INSPECT CONNECTING ROD OIL CLEARANCE

HINT:

Using SST, install and alternately tighten the 2 connecting rod bolts in several steps.

(a) Remove the connecting rod cap and connecting rod bearing.

HINT:

Click here

(b) Clean the crankshaft crank pin and connecting rod bearing.

(c) Check the crankshaft crank pin and connecting rod bearing for pitting and scratches.

HINT:

If the crank pin or upper connecting rod bearing is damaged, replace the connecting rod bearings. If necessary, replace the crankshaft.

(d) Lay a strip of Plastigage on the crank pin.

*a

Plastigage

(e) Check that the front mark of the connecting rod cap is facing the correct direction, and install the connecting rod bearing cap to the connecting rod.

*a

Front Mark

(f) Apply a light coat of engine oil to the threads and under the heads of the 2 connecting rod bolts.

(g) Using SST, install and alternately tighten the 2 connecting rod bolts in several steps.

SST: 09205-16011

Torque:

20 N·m {204 kgf·cm, 15 ft·lbf}

(h) Mark the front of each connecting rod bolt with paint.

*a

Paint Mark

*b

90°

Front of Engine

(i) Tighten the connecting rod bolts 90° as shown in the illustration.

NOTICE:

Do not turn the crankshaft during the measurement.

(j) Remove the 2 connecting rod bolts and connecting rod bearing cap.

(k) Measure the Plastigage at its widest point.

Standard Oil Clearance:

Maximum Oil Clearance

Specified Condition

0.070 mm

0.014 to 0.038 mm

0.00276 in.

0.000551 to 0.00150 in.

HINT:

  • If the oil clearance is more than the maximum, replace the connecting rod bearings. If necessary, replace the crankshaft.
  • If replacing a connecting rod bearing, select a new one with the same number as marked on the connecting rod cap. There are 3 sizes of standard connecting rod bearings, marked "1" , "2" , or "3" accordingly.

3. INSPECT CRANKSHAFT THRUST CLEARANCE

(a) Using a dial indicator, measure the crankshaft thrust clearance while prying the crankshaft back and forth with a screwdriver.

Standard Thrust Clearance:

Maximum Thrust Clearance

Specified Condition

0.18 mm

0.04 to 0.14 mm

0.00709 in.

0.00157 to 0.00551 in.

HINT:

If the thrust clearance is more than the maximum, replace the crankshaft thrust washer set. If necessary, replace the crankshaft.

Standard Thrust Washer Thickness:

2.43 to 2.48 mm (0.0957 to 0.0976 in.)

4. INSPECT CRANKSHAFT OIL CLEARANCE

(a) Check the crankshaft journals and crankshaft bearings for pitting and scratches.

(b) Install the crankshaft bearings.

HINT:

Click here

(c) Install the upper crankshaft thrust washers.

HINT:

Click here

(d) Clean each main journal and crankshaft bearing.

(e) Place the crankshaft on the cylinder block sub-assembly.

(f) Lay a strip of Plastigage across each journal.

*a

Plastigage

(g) Confirm the front marks and numbers, and place the 5 crankshaft bearing caps on the cylinder block sub-assembly.

HINT:

A number is marked on each crankshaft bearing cap to indicate the installation position.

*a

Front Mark and Number

(h) Install the crankshaft bearing caps.

NOTICE:

Do not turn the crankshaft.

HINT:

Click here

(i) Remove the crankshaft bearing caps.

HINT:

Click here

(j) Measure the Plastigage at its widest point.

(k) If replacing a crankshaft bearing, select a new one with the same number.

HINT:

  • If the number of the crankshaft bearing cannot be determined, select the correct crankshaft bearing number by adding together the numbers imprinted on the cylinder block sub-assembly and crankshaft. Then refer to the following table for the appropriate crankshaft bearing number. There are 4 sizes of standard crankshaft bearings, marked "1", "2", "3" or "4" accordingly.
  • Example: Cylinder block "4" + Crankshaft "3" = Total number 7 (Use crankshaft bearing "3")

5. INSPECT CYLINDER BLOCK FOR WARPAGE

(a) Using a precision straightedge and a feeler gauge, check the surfaces which contact the cylinder head gasket for warpage.

Maximum Warpage:

Specified Condition

0.05 mm

0.00197 in.

HINT:

If the warpage is more than the maximum, replace the cylinder block sub-assembly.

6. INSPECT CYLINDER BORE

(a) Using a cylinder gauge, measure the cylinder bore diameter at the positions (A) and (B) in the thrust and axial directions.

*a

Thrust Direction

*b

Axial Direction

Front of Engine

Maximum Diameter:

Reference Diameter (New Parts)

Specified Condition

80.500 to 80.513 mm

80.63 mm

3.16929 to 3.16980 in.

3.17 in.

Measurement Position:

Measurement Position

Cylinder Bore Position

(A)

10 mm (0.394 in.) from top edge

(B)

50 mm (1.97 in.) from top edge

HINT:

If the average diameter of 4 positions is more than the maximum, replace the cylinder block sub-assembly.

7. INSPECT NO. 1 OIL NOZZLE SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Push the check valve with a pin to check that it is not stuck.

HINT:

If the check valve is stuck, replace the No. 1 oil nozzle sub-assembly.

*a

Pin

(b) Apply air into (A). Check that air does not leak through (B).

HINT:

If air leaks, clean or replace the No. 1 oil nozzle sub-assembly.

(c) Push the check valve with a pin while applying air into (A). Check that air passes through (B).

HINT:

If air does not pass through (B), clean or replace the No. 1 oil nozzle sub-assembly.

*a

Pin

8. INSPECT PISTON SUB-ASSEMBLY WITH CONNECTING ROD

(a) Check the fitting condition between the piston and piston pin by trying to move the piston back and forth on the piston pin.

HINT:

If abnormal movement is felt, replace the piston and piston pin as a set.

9. INSPECT PISTON

(a) Using a micrometer, measure the piston diameter at a position 9.0 mm (0.354 in.) from the bottom of the piston (refer to the illustration).

Reference Piston Diameter (New Parts):

80.473 to 80.503 mm (3.16822 to 3.16940 in.)

HINT:

If the piston diameter is less than the minimum, replace the piston and piston pin as a set.

*a

9.0 mm

10. INSPECT PISTON OIL CLEARANCE

(a) Subtract the piston diameter measurement from the cylinder bore diameter measurement.

Maximum Oil Clearance:

Reference Oil Clearance (New Parts)

Specified Condition

-0.003 to 0.040 mm

0.08 mm

-0.000118 to 0.00157 in.

0.00315 in.

HINT:

If the piston oil clearance is more than the maximum, replace all the pistons with piston pins. If necessary, replace the cylinder block sub-assembly.

14. INSPECT CONNECTING ROD BOLT

(a) Using a vernier caliper, measure the diameter of the connecting rod bolt at several points within the area shown in the illustration.

Standard Diameter:

Minimum Diameter

Specified Condition

6.4 mm

6.6 to 6.7 mm

0.252 in.

0.260 to 0.264 in.

NOTICE:

  • Diameter measurements should be done at several points.
  • If the diameter is less than the minimum, replace the connecting rod bolt with a new one. Failure to do so may lead to engine damage.
  • If there is any thread deformation, replace the connecting rod bolt with a new one.

HINT:

If the diameter is less than the minimum, replace the connecting rod bolt.

*a

Measurement Area
